  "texts": [
    "The consistent performance of the TXtreme can be attributed to an effective data sampling policy employed during training, which ensures the model is learning from varying patterns and extreme values, enhancing its robustness and ability to generalize well across various domains.",
    "For the Solar dataset, the TXtreme demonstrates excellent generalization with a low percentage change of 3.21% in RMSE and 6.53% in MAE, indicating only a slight increase in error from training to test data.",
    "The Traffic dataset maintains a consistent error with zero change, underscoring the model's robustness in highly stable environments.",
    "In the Electricity dataset, the RMSE change is 6.64%, and the MAE change is 2.5%, reflecting strong generalization despite the inherently volatile nature of electricity usage patterns.",
    "For Web Traffic, the changes are minimal, with 3.23% for RMSE and 0.76% for MAE, suggesting the model's effective handling of web traffic fluctuations."
  ],
